# CQ8.3 (COMPETENCY_QUESTIONS.md concept 8): "Who proposed the most recent
# counter-offer?" -- "most recent" = a ma:CounterOffer that is not itself
# superseded by any other ma:CounterOffer.
#
# Added in the 2026-07-18 L5-push Round 3 pass. Uses `MINUS`, not
# `FILTER NOT EXISTS`: a real repro (see cq4.3's header for the full
# writeup) proved this engine's FILTER NOT EXISTS does not correlate the
# outer binding, so a first draft using it wrongly returned BOTH
# northgate-counter-1 and solvane-counter-2 instead of just the latter.
#
# Verified live (post-fix) against fixtures/case-2.ttl (1 row:
# solvane-counter-2 -> acquirer-solvane-analytics-group; northgate-counter-1
# is correctly excluded because solvane-counter-2 supersedes it) via the
# scratch consumer at /private/tmp/claude-501/-Users-sac-ggen/
# 70ac08c7-8655-49c4-baa2-018bc441bb4c/scratchpad/l5-round3-ma-case-study-pack/.

PREFIX ma: <http://seanchatmangpt.github.io/packs/ma-case-study#>
PREFIX prov: <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#>

SELECT ?latest ?proposer WHERE {
  ?latest a ma:CounterOffer ;
          prov:wasAttributedTo ?proposer .
  MINUS {
    ?later a ma:CounterOffer ; ma:supersedes ?latest .
  }
}
